'''Meulen''' is a [[Dutch language|Dutch]] [[toponymic surname]] meaning "mill" (modern Dutch ''molen'').<ref>[http://www.cbgfamilienamen.nl/nfb/detail_naam.php?nfd_naam=Meulen&info=aantal%20en%20verspreiding&operator=eq&taal= Meulen] at the Database of Surnames in The Netherlands.</ref> Notable people with the surname include:
*[[Ever Meulen]] (born 1946), pseudonym of Eddy Vermeulen, Belgian illustrator *[[Henry Meulen]] (1882–1978), British anarchist and economist *[[Manoe Meulen]] (born 1978), Dutch women's footballer
