{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}} [[File:Wiktor-Ormicki.jpg|thumb|upright|Wiktor Ormicki.]] '''Wiktor Ormicki''' (born ''Wiktor Rudolf Nusbaum'', 1898–1941) was a [[Poland|Polish]] geographer and cartographer, a university professor of Jewish descent. A specialist in [[economical geography]] and [[demography]], he served at various posts in the [[Jagiellonian University]], [[Wolna Wszechnica]], Higher Trade School of Kraków and [[Lwów University]]. Arrested by the Germans during [[World War II]], he was murdered in the [[Mauthausen-Gusen concentration camp]].
